reviews.review: amazing movie! perfect way to end the skywalker saga! highly reccommend!

This movie brought me closure for every disappointment from the Last Jedi! A lot of fan service, but still kept me guessing til the end. Ignore the haters! This is possibly my favorite in the whole series!
Same movie but with more boring characters.  Started to nod off near the end.

the movie seemed like:
(1) a sequel to a movie that was never made; AND
(2) a YouTube supercut of a TV show that was at least 10 episodes long...

The Rise of Skywalker is a great ending to the sequel trilogy. It ignores a majority of The Last Jedi to bring it back in line to what a Star Wars film should be. The main characters all get the screen time they deserve and characters that weren't good in The Last Jedi are great! As expected, the visuals are top notch and the music is the best it's ever been. The pacing is fast but I don't have an issue with that because there's so much in this movie. I'm glad JJ Abrams was able to give us a satisfying conclusion, especially after The Last Jedi.
Full of surprises. Will definitely keep you watching.

WAY too long........ugh.........best part though was the healing events where they used their hands and had awesome outcomes........love the franchise, love star wars love the characters just WAY too long
Loved how they tied parts of the story together with older episodes!

How to ruin even the old movies of the franchise lesson 2 (The Last Jedi was lesson 1). The first half seemed more decent but still...Rey is faaaar too powerful and perfect, no struggle at all and she never fails (unlike Luke) so she kinda feels not real or human. Palpatine seems forced in just to buy fans back and makes all the sacrifices made by Luke, Anakin and pretty much everyone in the old movies kinda irrelevant.
Plot makes no sense at all, the pacing is BAD, everything happens way too fast. Also...blowing up things again? SO.MANY.PLOT.HOLES.!
Still a little better than The Last Jedi....but it's kinda like saying piss is better than shit.
The last 35-45 nimutes was too rushed.  Should've made it into a 2 part.  It was a decent movie.
